Barcelona have completed the signing of Chile goalkeeper Claudio Bravo on a four-year deal from Real Sociedad.

The club say Bravo will 'share' goalkeeping duties with fellow new arrival Marc-Andre ter Stegen in place of the departed Victor Valdes.

Barca announced the signing on their Twitter page, and described Bravo as a goalkeeper who 'offers agility and experience'.

